General Motors Corp and PPGIndustries Inc announced jointly that they had signed anagreement that will give PPG responsibility for operating thepaint shop in GM's Buick Reatta Craft Center here.    The Reatta is a two-seat luxury car that will be introducedin the spring of 1988, said GM.    The companies described the agreement as an arrangementaimed at integrating GM's auto production expertise with PPG'scoatings expertise.    Under the agreement, PPG's and GM's paint operating staffat the center will be consolidated under the PPG area manager.    Reuter&#3;